The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 12:45 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  fell 0.6 percent to 12,511.79, while the
Colcap Index declined 0.5 percent to 1,563.37.  Empresa de Telecomunicaciones de Bogota SA (ETB)  , the
phone company serving Colombiaâ€™s capital, rose 1.3 percent to
449 pesos. The company said it will use the network of Colombia
Movil, or Tigo, to begin offering virtual mobile phone services
in the second week of January, according to a regulatory filing
Dec. 16.  Isagen SA (ISAGEN)  , a Colombian energy company, rose 0.2
percent to 2,085 pesos. The company is waiting for the U.S.
Securities and Exchange Commission to decide on approval for
level-1  American Depositary Receipts  in New York, Juan Diego
Ortiz, director of financial resources, told Portafolio
yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
